        <body>
            <div type="edition"><!-- transcription goes here -->
                <ab><lb n="1"/><expan><abbr>D</abbr><ex>is</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>anibus</ex></expan>
                <lb n="2"/><persName><name type="gentilicium" key="Valerius"><expan><abbr>Val</abbr><ex>erii</ex></expan></name> <name type="cognomen" key="Valerianus">Valerian<choice><corr>i</corr><sic>l</sic></choice></name></persName> fe
                <lb n="3" break="no"/>cit <persName><name type="gentilicium" key="Aurelius"><expan><abbr>Aur</abbr><ex>elius</ex></expan></name> <name type="cognomen" key="Scupus">Scupus</name></persName> <expan><abbr>mil</abbr><ex>es</ex></expan>
                <lb n="4"/><expan><abbr>pr</abbr><ex>aetorianus</ex></expan> municipi
                <lb n="5"/>suo <expan><abbr>b</abbr><ex>e</ex><abbr>n</abbr><ex>e</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>m</abbr><ex>erenti</ex></expan>.
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <p>"Aurelius Scupus, praetorian soldier, made this for the divine shades of Valerius Valerianus, his well-deserving townsman."</p>
            </div>            
            <div type="commentary"><!-- notes go here -->
            <p>At line 2, Wilson and CIL print "Valeriani" with no comment; however, the carver appears to have written a letter "L" at the end of the name
                    "Valerian-", with a cross bar with serif attached to the bottom of the hasta. I have corrected to "I".</p></div>
            
